    "This perspective allows for alternative views on human embodiment in technology.",
    "In section two, I point to two different aspects of human engagement in technology that depend highly on a person's re-evoking of their past encounters with others.",
    "These occurrences depend to a large extent on verbal activity.",
    "In section three, I argue that the languaging perspective, which treats language as human activity rather than an autonomous system used for communication (Cowley 2019), precedes human presencing.",
    "Treating language as activity emphasizes a person's ecological and sociocultural embedding."
